      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SNEAKY SESSION (8) settled back in the run last time out and finished off strongly, beaten 1.4L at this track last time out. The slight rise in trip shouldn't be an issue and maybe the tactics change last start did the trick. Rates well on that effort and she can go a couple better. ENCOSTA DE MONEY (4) was just too fat back to threaten on debut when missing the start and ending up at the back of the pack. This is a suitable race however and with improvement to come, he can feature in the finish. RUBICK DELIGHT (5) is second-up here and felt the pinch over 1400m fresh. Her trial coming in was very good however and the drop in trip may be the trick. GILES (1) missed as favourite last start at Bunbury and has claims on that run. GIGI GOGO (7) is in the mix.",
